<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4921] HTable initialization looks for EMPTY_START_ROW</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4921</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The HTable initialization does something like this : &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.connection.locateRegion(tableName, HConstants.EMPTY_START_ROW);&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What is the rationale behind this ? What would happen if this region is in flight ? I ran into a problem where I disabled the first region of the table and now I can&apos;t create an HTable instance to this table.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Disabling the first region is like disabling the entire table from a client perspective. I feel this is not the correct behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
